					<td background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/trick.jpg" width="100%" valign="top">


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Many Cleric TIPS for you</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Daluin</a> | 
		            9/1/2000 4:23:16 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Couple suggestions:<BR>
<BR>
1) Learn how and when to heal. For instance I (at lvl 37) mainly use GHeal but also have Superior heal in mem.  GHeal heals ~300 hp. and superior heal heals ~580 hp.  What this means is when I heal someone for 300 or 580 hp, the mob sees this as me doing 300 or 580 damage to him.  Best thing to do is know your tanks and get a feel for how low they can go before you need to heal (personally I wont let them drop below 50%).  If the tank can dish out enough damage before you heal, it lessens the chance that the mob will aggro on you.  This takes practice to get good at because if you wait too long (depending on the pull) your tank might die before the spell is done casting (thats the main reason why I dont like them below 50%).<BR>
Talk this over with the tanks, some get nervous when they are down only 1 bubble health.  Remind him that you are aware of that.  I find most tanks are comfortable when I heal them at 50%.  Course after the fight I heal them to full  ;)<BR>
<BR>
2) Learn to use more than one stun (chain stunning)! For instance I have stun, holy might and force. I will usually pick the higher 2 and use them to stop a casting mob from doing spell damage (or healing).  What you do is watch the CHAT WINDOW (NOT THE ANIMATIONS).. Soon as you see &quot;A lizard begins to cast..&quot; you immediatly cast one of the stuns.  Then soon as it begins to cast again you fire off the second stun.  Doing this with 1 mob and 2 stuns will allow for one of the stun spells to always be available. Sometimes it will be resisted of course. If it is, try dropping to 2 lower stun spells if it happens frequently. Obviously if you are fighting deep reds it wont work at all.  <BR>
<BR>
Another thing about chain stunning... If the pulls are going easy and there is no risk to me going OOM, I will also chain stun non casting mobs! Why? Well a mob that isnt doing damage while stunned means less healing my tank needs  ;)<BR>
<BR>
3) Say you are in a small group WITHOUT an enchanter, snarer or rooter.  In a bad pull situation you can somewhat perform crowd control as follows... Lets say the tank pulls 2 mobs. What you do is target the mob that the tank ISNT fighting and root it. Once you root it tell the tank to back away so he can fight 1 mob while you (hopefully) can keep the other one rooted.<BR>
<BR>
More on root.. If you are with a druid (or anyone who can snare), let them snare and DONT use root *IF* you are in a zone where trains are easily created (cazic comes to mind).  The reason is this, once the root breaks if the mob was running from you in the first place, he will now bolt off at full speed.  If you fail to re-root him, get ready for a train.  Snare is usually much better than root because it slows the mob down. And once the mob is damaged it will stop moving entirely!<BR>
<BR>
4) Always keep your group aware of how much mana you have! &quot;/g 50%&quot; etc... And without a doubt if you are in a nasty fight DO NOT WAIT TILL OOM TO WARN THEM!<BR>
<BR>
5) If a mob aggro's on you during a nasty pull, DO NOT RUN LIKE AN IDIOT! Stand there, disengage and wait for the tank or enchanter to peel it off you.  If you must, make a macro that says something like &quot;/g Healer getting hit, please taunt I cant heal&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
A note on this: If this continues to happen and they dont taunt off you, leave the group if they are unwilling to work together. HOWEVER, make sure it wasnt your fault in the first place (I.E. Did you heal WAY too soon?  Are you trying to be a wizard?..).<BR>
<BR>
6) Find out what classes are in your group?  See that guy at 50% HP all the time?  He might be cannibalizing and doesnt want a heal.  Healing him is like transferring mana to him. What good is a OOM cleric when the necro is FM?  NOTE: Im strickly talking about between pulls! Most people who canniblize tell me to heal them when they are down to 2 bubbles DURING a fight.  They will tell you to save your mana so there is less downtime.<BR>
<BR>
7) Buff the tanks. Buff the enchanter! Make sure that all the tanks are /assisting the main tank. No sense in everyone fighting their own fight (causing you to heal 5 people instead of 1 or 2).  Watch the enchanter closely. If they are down 2 bubbles of HP kick a heal, they are not tanks and could easily DIE before your heal goes off! And if he dies in a bad pull, chances are high that you are next.<BR>
<BR>
8) Divine Aura &amp; Divine Barrier. I *always* have at least 1 in mem!  If I dont use it when im in evac mode (tank said ZONE!), I will use it as a reverse taunt!  If your tanks are busy in a bad pull, cast DA and back off. This will almost always cause those mobs to go back to the tank(s) saving them the trouble of taunting during a bad pull.<BR>
<BR>
9) If you are in a bad group (every pull is a bad pull, tank dont taunt, wizz burns too early, tanks are breaking mez, nobody is using /assist, etc) try to talk with them.  Dont be rude! Some people are still learning the ropes and are willing to listen if you say things in a nice way.  If they refuse to listen, bail out and find some better partners before these get you killed.<BR>
<BR>
10) Is there another healer in the group? Cleric or hybrid?  If there is make arrangements ahead of time! Who will be the main healer? How should you notify the backup healer when he is needed?  If 2 clerics figure out who will heal who (you heal 3 and ill heal 3).<BR>
<BR>
11) If you have 2 clerics in group, switch off on the buffs! Let him cast valor while you cast guard. Whatever, point is it will save you mana.  Work together, as a group should  ;)<BR>
<BR>
- Have fun with your cleric, it can be boring at times but in the right group I find im rarely OOM (if ever except for the occasional pull).  Make fun macro's to brighten the mood and boost morale &quot;Daluin Scores a Critical Hit(-1)&quot;..   Once you are over 35th the spell book is no longer in your face so at least you can see the action. If your mana is good and you are comfortable with your group, get up and mele a bit if you want!  Have fun, thats all that matters!<BR>
<BR>
Daluin<BR>
37th Season Cleric of Karana
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
